reviewText:
Masterful concept movie by a couple of real shrewd young guys which takes the country by storm. I loved the following:
1. Grainy video all the way through, no production values, no sharp photography, so low-budget it looks homemade;
2. No monsters or witches shown;
3. Very subtle night sounds create more horror than anything else;
4. Night scene in old house has to rate as one of the more terrifying scenes in movie history;
5. Bag of bloody teeth, weird stick figures and effigies in trees set a mood of impending doom;
6. Great performances by the three main characters; totally believable.

This film made buckets of money. The filmmakers pulled a fast one, but they richly deserve every cent they made.

Last point: the amount that you hated this film is directly disproportional to your intelligence and sophistication. Translation: if you did not like or appreciate the movie, you are a stupid hayseed; you need to get out more.
